Changes in Version 1.0-1

  o The German Economic Review paper was finally published: Wagner and
    Zeileis (2019). Heterogeneity and Spatial Dependence of Regional Growth
    in the EU: A Recursive Partitioning Approach. German Economic Review,
    20(1), 67-82. doi: 10.1111/geer.12146. The preprint version is still at
    https://eeecon.uibk.ac.at/~zeileis/papers/Wagner+Zeileis-2019.pdf

  o Roger Bivand joined as a contributor to the package and adapted the
    code to transition from the old "spdep" to the new "spatialreg" package.
    Furthermore, impacts were added and extra arguments passed through to
    lagsarlm() from the lagsarlmtree() function.


Changes in Version 1.0-0

  o First CRAN release of the "lagsarlmtree" package accompanying the acceptance
    of the corresponding manuscript "Heterogeneity and Spatial Dependence of
    Regional Growth in the EU: A Recursive Partitioning Approach" in the German
    Economic Review (doi:10.1111/geer.12146). A preprint version is available
    online at: https://eeecon.uibk.ac.at/~zeileis/papers/Wagner+Zeileis-2019.pdf

  o Replication materials for the manuscript are available in the package as:
    demo("GrowthNUTS2", package = "lagsarlmtree")

